article.headline: Colorado St. 77, Colorado 62
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Travis Franklin had 22 points and 10 rebounds leading Colorado State to a 77-62 victory over Colorado Thursday night. Franklin was two points short of his career high. Dorian Green added 21 points for Colorado State (6-3). Andy Ogide had 13 points and the Rams hit 30 of 39 free throws. The Rams won for the fourth time in five games and held Colorado to a season-low 62 points. Alec Burks led Colorado (6-4) with 22 points. Cory Higgins had 12 points. Higgins had an off night, shooting 1 for 10 from the field and 0 for 4 on 3-pointers. He was 10 of 11 from the free-throw line and reached 1,000 points for his career.
